# Beads/Dolt: intentionally NO hydration here (anton-vqgw).
#
# This used to chain `.beads/hooks/post-merge`, which re-imports Dolt data after `git pull`/merge.
# That import is redundant for an anton-driven repo — the runner pushes Dolt explicitly on every
# write — and it is not harmless: hydration replaces local rows from an older synced snapshot, so a
# bead closed after that snapshot was taken silently reverts to open. Closed epics were observed
# flipping back to open across merges (bd history showed four closed->open flips in one day).
#
# Export/push stays chained in .husky/pre-commit and .husky/pre-push — those publish local state and
# are safe. Only the inbound hydration (post-merge, post-checkout) is dropped.
